//tests: 

------------------------------------------------------------------------

CHUNKED BINARY FILE:

create big.txt --> head -c 100000 /dev/urandom > big.txt 
- gives you 100kb of binary garbage (not readable text) 

Post it in chuncks with this command:

curl -v http://localhost:8080/uploads \
  -H "Transfer-Encoding: chunked" \
  --data-binary "@big.txt"

-------------------------------------------------------------------------

CHUNKED TEXT FILE: 

create big.txt --> yes "this is a line of text" | head -n 5000 > big.txt
- gives you 5000 lines of readable content 

Post it with this command: 

curl -v http://localhost:8080/uploads \
  -H "Transfer-Encoding: chunked" \
  --data-binary "@test.txt"

-------------------------------------------------------------------------

CHUNKED TEXT/PLAIN: 

curl -v http://localhost:8080/uploads \
  -H "Content-Type: text/plain" \
  -H "Transfer-Encoding: chunked" \
  --data-binary "hello again from plain text"

-------------------------------------------------------------------------

CHUNKED FORM FIELD: 

curl -v http://localhost:8080/uploads \
  -H "Content-Type: application/x-www-form-urlencoded" \
  -H "Transfer-Encoding: chunked" \
  --data-binary "username=tester&message=chunked%20rocks"

-------------------------------------------------------------------------

CHUNKED MULTIPART/FORM-DATA:

Create test.txt --> yes "this is a stupid test" | head -n 5 > test.txt

curl -v http://localhost:8080/uploads \
  -H "Transfer-Encoding: chunked" \
  -F "file=@test.txt"

-------------------------------------------------------------------------

SIEGE STRESS TESTS:

siege -b -c 10 -t 10s "http://127.0.0.1:8080/empty.html"
siege -b -c 10 -t 5s "http://127.0.0.1:8080/cgi-bin/guestbook_display.php"



